The engine under
  plugins/deep-research-skill/skills/deep-research-skill/engine/
is an original, from-scratch implementation with a claim-centric,
post-collection design (see docs/REBUILD_PLAN.md).

Several algorithms it (re)implements are standard / textbook:
  - Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF)
  - Maximal Marginal Relevance (MMR)
  - nDCG@k, precision@k, Jaccard similarity
  - SQLite WAL + FTS5 accumulation patterns

These were studied for reference in the MIT-licensed "last30days" skill
by mvanhorn. No source code was copied; the engine is written from
scratch. The reference skill's MIT license permits reuse with
attribution, which this notice provides.
